{"word":"ἀνιαρός","slug":"ἀνιαρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνιαρός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνιάω'><el>ἀνιάω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>In Hom and <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b> always <el>ανῑ-</el>, in other Poets <el>ανι-.</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>grievous, troublesome, annoying</i>, of persons, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>ἐχθροῖς ἀνιαροί</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, of animals, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἀνιαρῶς</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things,<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>painful, grievous, distressing</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>ἀνιηρέστερος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>grieved, distressed</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ρῶς</el> <i>wretchedly</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}